│ memory, GVN treats them as "pure" function calls. Since their arguments are identical,  │
│ GVN considers them to be congruent and thus redundant. This incorrect assumption is the │
│ trigger for the faulty optimization.                                                    │
│                                                                                         │
│ ### 3. Root Cause Analysis                                                              │
│                                                                                         │
│ The root cause lies in how `BasicAA` models the memory effects of the                   │
│ `llvm.dx.resource.handlefrombinding` intrinsic. This DirectX-specific intrinsic, while  │
│ returning a handle (which is not a pointer), has side effects. It interacts with the    │
│ DirectX runtime's internal state to create or retrieve a resource handle. Multiple      │
│ calls, even with the same arguments, are not necessarily pure or idempotent and should  │
│ not be considered to have `NoModRef` behavior relative to each other.                   │
│                                                                                         │
