│ `%bufExit`) as redundant. It then attempts to perform PRE (Partial Redundancy           │
│ Elimination) by sinking the computation. The call `%bufExit` is in the `CSMain.exit`    │
│ block, which is post-dominated by the block `for.body.i.lr.ph` where `%buf` is defined. │
│ GVN decides to replace `%bufExit` with a PHI node in `CSMain.exit`.                     │
│                                                                                         │
│ This new PHI node would have two incoming values:                                       │
│ 1.  The result of the original `%buf` call, coming from the loop path (`for.body.i`).   │
│ 2.  A new call to `llvm.dx.resource.handlefrombinding` that GVN would insert in the     │
│ `entry` block, for the path that bypasses the loop.                                     │
│                                                                                         │
