│     return FMRB_ModRef;                                                                 │
│                                                                                         │
│   case Intrinsic::launder_invariant_group:                                              │
│   case Intrinsic::strip_invariant_group:                                                │
│     // The invariant group intrinsics are readnone.                                     │
│ ```                                                                                     │
│                                                                                         │
│ ### 5. Conclusion                                                                       │
│                                                                                         │
│ By updating `BasicAliasAnalysis` to correctly identify                                  │
│ `llvm.dx.resource.handlefrombinding` as having memory side effects (`ModRef`), we       │
│ provide accurate information to downstream passes. GVN will no longer consider the two  │
│ calls to be redundant, and it will not attempt the faulty transformation that creates a │
│ `token`-typed PHI node. This resolves the verifier crash and ensures the semantics of   │
│ the DirectX intrinsics are respected during optimization.                               │
