│ The user wants me to fix an LLVM bug that causes a crash in the GVN pass. The verifier  │
│ fails with the error "PHI nodes cannot have token type!".                               │
│                                                                                         │
│ Based on the provided root cause analysis, the issue stems from `BasicAliasAnalysis`    │
│ incorrectly reporting `NoModRef` for the `llvm.dx.resource.handlefrombinding`           │
│ intrinsic. This intrinsic, specific to DirectX, creates a resource handle and has side  │
│ effects. Because `BasicAA` considers it side-effect-free, GVN incorrectly identifies    │
│ two calls to it as redundant. GVN then attempts to perform Partial Redundancy           │
│ Elimination (PRE), which involves creating a PHI node. The return type of the intrinsic │
│ is a `token`-like type, and creating a PHI node of this type is illegal, leading to the │
│ verifier crash.                                                                         │
│                                                                                         │
│ The fix is to teach `BasicAA` about the side effects of this intrinsic. I will modify   │
│ `BasicAAResult::getModRefBehavior` in `llvm/lib/Analysis/BasicAliasAnalysis.cpp` to     │
│ recognize `Intrinsic::dx_resource_handlefrombinding` and return `FMRB_ModRef`,          │
│ indicating that it may read from and write to memory. This will prevent GVN from        │
│ performing the incorrect optimization.                                                  │
│                                                                                         │
│ I will now apply this change.                                                           │
│                                                                                         │
